=== INTEREST RATES ===

Base annual rates by loan type:
- Federal Subsidized: 5.53% -- undergraduate, need-based
- Federal Unsubsidized: 5.53% -- undergraduate, no need requirement
- Federal PLUS: 8.08% -- parent PLUS / grad PLUS
- Refinanced: 6.99% -- refinanced through a private lender
- Private: 9.95% -- private market, varies by credit

These are defaults for new loans. A loan may carry a different rate if
originated under a promotional program.


=== AUTOPAY DISCOUNT ===

Enrolling in autopay reduces the interest rate by 0.25 percentage points
for all loan types, for as long as autopay remains active. If the borrower
cancels autopay, the rate reverts to the base rate immediately.


=== PAYMENT ALLOCATION ===

When a payment is received, apply in this order:
1. Pay down all accrued interest first
2. Remaining amount reduces the principal balance

Interest is charged daily at (annual_rate / 365) * current_balance.
interest_portion + principal_portion must always equal the payment amount.


=== GRACE PERIOD ===

After graduation or dropping below half-time enrollment, federal loans
enter a grace period before repayment begins:
- Federal Subsidized: 6 months (no interest accrual during grace)
- Federal Unsubsidized: 6 months (interest accrues normally)
- Federal PLUS: no grace -- repayment begins at disbursement
- Private: no grace (varies by lender; assume none)
- Refinanced: no grace

During grace, loan status is 'in_grace'. Once grace ends, status
transitions to 'in_repayment'.


=== COSIGNER REQUIREMENTS ===

Cosigners are required for private loans and recommended for refinanced
loans.

Cosigner release eligibility: after 24 consecutive on-time payments, the
borrower may apply to release the cosigner. Release requires the borrower
to meet credit and income criteria on their own.


=== HARDSHIP OPTIONS ===

Deferment:
- Maximum: 36 months
- Eligibility: federal loans only (unemployment or economic hardship)
- Interest accrual: only unsubsidized federal loans accrue interest

Forbearance:
- Maximum: 12 months
- Eligibility: all loan types (discretionary hardship -- medical, short-term)
- Interest accrual: all loans accrue interest

Deferment and forbearance pause required payments. Use deferment first if
the borrower is eligible -- it is cheaper.


=== DEFAULT TIMELINE ===

- Delinquent: after 90 days of missed payments
- Default: after 270 days of non-payment

Defaulted federal loans may be subject to wage garnishment and tax-refund
offset. Defaulted private loans go to collections and damage the borrower's
credit severely.


=== PREPAYMENT ===

All loan types allow prepayment without penalty. Extra payments apply to
principal after covering accrued interest.
